description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Bank Services at CUH are currently seeking Registered Nurses to work within our Critical Care areas, John Farman Intensive Care Unit (JFICU) , Neurosciences Critical Care Unit (NCCU) Intermediate Dependency Area (IDA). Staff Bank provides the flexibility of working hours which would enable you to achieve a good work and home life balance, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will receive a full induction to the critical areas at CUH and will have an opportunity to undertake paid study days such as the Management of Deteriorating Patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The level of payment will also reflect the specialist skills required for these area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer Bank shifts on either an ad hoc or placement basis. Undertaking a placement offers you the consistency of working in one area but still allows you to retain flexibility as to the days and shifts worked.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for motivated individuals who will be responsible for the assessment of patient needs, and the development, implementation and evaluation of care. If you feel this might be you, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lisa Enoch, Critical Care Education Lead on 01223 216838&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJackie FarrerJob titleStaff Bank ManagerEmail addressjackie.farrer@addenbrookes.nhs.ukTelephone number01223 596300&lt;/p&gt;
